comments: If you have difficulty with any level math course, Ms. Borynski is the professor to take. She has great handouts which you can use to take notes, she breaks down complex concepts into understandable parts and she links common concepts so that you can see the big picture. If you want to learn and pass any math class, take this professor.

comments: The content of the class (mat 152) can be a bit difficult if you don\'t put the time in. However, Mrs. Borynski is very clear and articulate. Her lectures can be very long and drone on, very monotone. She is willing to help and if you put in the work I bet you can get an A in her class. Don\'t buy the physical textbook, just the online code.

comments: Mrs. Borynski has been one of the best math teachers I have ever had. Her lectures are pretty long and thorough so expect to be sitting for a while. Although her class is pretty boring, she makes things easy to understand. Make sure to take good notes and pay attention. No quizzes, Lots of HWK, 3/4 tests and 2 projects.
